A fine but weak wine made mostly in the Silver Marches and in small pockets of Faerun, this reddish wine has a country taste to it and is served throughout the Sword Coast  and the North but is not known elsewhere.

Considered one of the finest wines made in Faerun, and the sweetest, this amber colored wine comes only from Calimport and its brewing process is a mystery. Some dare say that magical grapes are used in the mix.
A popular drink in Chessenta but otherwise unknown in Faerun with the exception of some larger taverns in Aglorond. Known for its ultra bitter sting that often causes choking, hence the name.

Nobody knows exactly where this brew came from but rumors say the recipe came from the realm of chaos itself.
One thing is for certain drinking this brew changes a man (or woman).

Also known as Dragon's Eye Beer this bitter nasty smelling ale has a dark brown color. It is well known due to the trading nations advertising of the beer and it's natural popularity. It is found in Sembia, Cormyr, the Dales, the Moonsea, the Vilhon Reach, Sword Coast, and the Vast and has appeared even in the Dragon Reach.
The favored drink of the Drow and a main export from Menzoberranzan. This glowing blue drink is said to cause hallucinations and be quite addictive, leading many to ask what is in it.

The most popular drink of Dwarves throughout Faerun and made primarily in the Great Rift. This ale can be found anywhere in Faerun at a high price due to importing costs but is a bit cheaper in the North after a band of Gold Dwarves set up shop at Hellgate Keep.
Made by the frost dwarves of Icewind Dale and not found anywhere else except a few taverns in the North. Most dwarves find this wine unworthy of them and most humans find it too strong for a wine.
This silvery Elven mead, like the name, comes only from the Elven city of Evereska and is not exported often to any non-Elven nations of city-states. It is a sweet mead that remains light.

The famed Elven drink of choice is seen by many non Elves to be water and weak. In fact it is an wine made for the taste of Elves alone. It is a dark blue wine and very rich and kept in supply by many bartenders across Faerun.
This reddish orange wine is sour and hot to the taste but a favorite among the realms. It is one of Baldur's Gate's best resources as it is sold all over Faerun and is unique in taste and texture.

This brew  was made by a brewer named kawaresksenjajok who bought
the recipe from a acheologist who found it in  some old ruins from the creator race.
be carefull though the weak of stature may be killed by this strong brew.
Spirits, usually made from distilled grains, are very potent and should not be taken lightly.
A favorite drink of Hobbits and the famed drink of Luiren. It has a dark amber color and a thick texture. It is strong, bubbly and sweet and is imported to various taverns in the Realms.

This wine was made from lilac blossoms, making it very sweet to the taste, but very strong.

Made of the rarest material only found within the land of Tuat, imported by ded by arrangement with Sarah.

This ancient fine wine has been aged for thousands of years and is only found as a treasure within ancient tombs and buried cities. It has a silvery blue texture and said to give the drinker enhanced charismatic powers

This brew is made by the orcs as a means to hold contests with eachother. Each orc gets 10 drinks the first orc to drop unconscious is the looser. Although this brew is a mildly intoxicating drink it is known that sometimes by accident a poisoness ingredient slips into the brewing barrel.

What is in Scurrd? What, indeed. Scurrd. just seems to find its way to where it can do the most harm. It's truly vicious.

It cannot be smelled by the elderly...
It cannot be held by small children... 
It is Scurrd, and woe be to ye that take it to your tongue.
Spirits, usually made from distilled grains, are very potent and should not be taken lightly.

A very popular drink exported from the Dales more than any other. This dark strong ale is the drink of paladins since it is not only named after Torm but made by a follower of the faith. This ale has not appeared in the Moonsea for political reasons but is rampant in the Dales, Vast, Sembia, Cormyr, Vilhon Reach and even the Sword Coast.

Uncle Volo's Bathtub Gin - quality liquour at a great low cost! A beautifully rendered portrait of Volothamp Geddarm in a rakish pose graces the label.

"It's the secret to my success with the ladies!" - Volo













Commercial use of Volothamp Geddarm's image by permission. All rights reserved Amnian Fine Ales, Ltd.

(small lettering)
Medical guild warning: may cause gastric distress. Not for use by nursing mothers, pregnant women, scholars, or small children.
Either a dark red or pale yellow, wine is made from the pressing of grapes that have been fermented and aged.

A common white wine made in the North and sold in other cold climates. This surprisingly strong tasting (although not quite effecting) wine is often drunk by nobility but can be found in smaller taverns in the North, Sword Coast, Dales, Cormyr, Moonsea and the Vast.

This emerald green brew is sometimes referred to as "The Green Fairy" due to both it's emerald color and "inspirational" mental effects. This is a strong herbal liqueur distilled with a great number of flavorful herbs like anise, licorice, hyssop, veronica, fennel, lemon balm, angelica and, of course, wormwood. This drink is popular with many intellectual and artistic individuals as it is reputed to enhance creative thinking.

It should be noted that this liqueur does not mix well and is toxic in large quantities.
